?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Vasiliy Kochergin","active":false,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"updated":"2014-07-03T09:06:37.899-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10005","id":"10005","name":"DNS"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/11504","id":"11504","name":"EC2"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"*Assessment*\r\n\r\nCurrently, the cloud property experimental.dns.recursive.enabled only affects recursive lookups done from within an instance.  Is there a way to disable recursive lookups from clients that are outside the cloud that are doing recursive lookups against public DNS names of instances (e.g. similar to the bind DNS [recursive|http://www.zytrax.com/books/dns/ch7/queries.html#recursion] configuration option under the [view|http://www.zytrax.com/books/dns/ch7/view.html] clause)?  This is to stop DNS amplifier attacks.  A good example of this can be found [here|http://www.zytrax.com/books/dns/ch7/view.html] under _'split' DNS using views_ section.\r\n\r\n*Signs*\r\n\r\n_With experimental.dns.recursive.enabled set to true_\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n### From within an instance ###\r\n\r\nubuntu@euca-172-17-113-149:~$ dig www.google.com @10.104.1.216 +recurse\r\n\r\n; <<>> DiG 9.9.2-P1 <<>> www.google.com @10.104.1.216 +recurse\r\n;; global options: +cmd\r\n;; Got answer:\r\n;; ->>HEADER<<- opcode: QUERY, status: NOERROR, id: 34613\r\n;; flags: qr rd ra; QUERY: 1, ANSWER: 5, AUTHORITY: 4, ADDITIONAL: 5\r\n\r\n;; OPT PSEUDOSECTION:\r\n; EDNS: version: 0, flags:; udp: 4096\r\n;; QUESTION SECTION:\r\n;www.google.com.\t\t\tIN\tA\r\n\r\n;; ANSWER SECTION:\r\nwww.google.com.\t\t212\tIN\tA\t74.125.224.115\r\nwww.google.com.\t\t212\tIN\tA\t74.125.224.116\r\nwww.google.com.\t\t212\tIN\tA\t74.125.224.112\r\nwww.google.com.\t\t212\tIN\tA\t74.125.224.113\r\nwww.google.com.\t\t212\tIN\tA\t74.125.224.114\r\n\r\n;; AUTHORITY SECTION:\r\ngoogle.com.\t\t18150\tIN\tNS\tns1.google.com.\r\ngoogle.com.\t\t18150\tIN\tNS\tns3.google.com.\r\ngoogle.com.\t\t18150\tIN\tNS\tns2.google.com.\r\ngoogle.com.\t\t18150\tIN\tNS\tns4.google.com.\r\n\r\n;; ADDITIONAL SECTION:\r\nns1.google.com.\t\t26603\tIN\tA\t216.239.32.10\r\nns3.google.com.\t\t26603\tIN\tA\t216.239.36.10\r\nns2.google.com.\t\t26603\tIN\tA\t216.239.34.10\r\nns4.google.com.\t\t26603\tIN\tA\t216.239.38.10\r\n\r\n;; Query time: 138 msec\r\n;; SERVER: 10.104.1.216#53(10.104.1.216)\r\n;; WHEN: Wed Oct 16 16:32:25 2013\r\n;; MSG SIZE  rcvd: 259\r\n\r\n### from outside the cloud ###\r\n\r\neuca-prod-1-82:~ haroldspencerjr$ dig euca-10-104-7-10.eucalyptus.euca-hasp.eucalyptus-systems.com @10.104.1.216 +recurse\r\n\r\n; <<>> DiG 9.8.3-P1 <<>> euca-10-104-7-10.eucalyptus.euca-hasp.eucalyptus-systems.com @10.104.1.216 +recurse\r\n;; global options: +cmd\r\n;; Got answer:\r\n;; ->>HEADER<<- opcode: QUERY, status: NOERROR, id: 51162\r\n;; flags: qr aa rd ra; QUERY: 1, ANSWER: 1, AUTHORITY: 0, ADDITIONAL: 0\r\n\r\n;; QUESTION SECTION:\r\n;euca-10-104-7-10.eucalyptus.euca-hasp.eucalyptus-systems.com. IN A\r\n\r\n;; ANSWER SECTION:\r\neuca-10-104-7-10.eucalyptus.euca-hasp.eucalyptus-systems.com. 60 IN A 10.104.7.10\r\n\r\n;; Query time: 235 msec\r\n;; SERVER: 10.104.1.216#53(10.104.1.216)\r\n;; WHEN: Wed Oct 16 12:29:48 2013\r\n;; MSG SIZE  rcvd: 94\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n_With  experimental.dns.recursive.enabled set to false_\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n### from within the instance ###\r\n\r\nubuntu@euca-172-17-113-149:~$ dig www.google.com @10.104.1.216 +recurse\r\n;; Warning: query response not set\r\n\r\n; <<>> DiG 9.9.2-P1 <<>> www.google.com @10.104.1.216 +recurse\r\n;; global options: +cmd\r\n;; Got answer:\r\n;; ->>HEADER<<- opcode: QUERY, status: SERVFAIL, id: 43260\r\n;; flags: rd ad; QUERY: 1, ANSWER: 0, AUTHORITY: 0, ADDITIONAL: 0\r\n;; WARNING: recursion requested but not available\r\n\r\n;; QUESTION SECTION:\r\n;www.google.com.\t\t\tIN\tA\r\n\r\n;; Query time: 21 msec\r\n;; SERVER: 10.104.1.216#53(10.104.1.216)\r\n;; WHEN: Wed Oct 16 16:31:27 2013\r\n;; MSG SIZE  rcvd: 32\r\n\r\n### from outside the cloud ###\r\n\r\neuca-prod-1-82:~ haroldspencerjr$ dig euca-10-104-7-10.eucalyptus.euca-hasp.eucalyptus-systems.com @10.104.1.216 +recurse\r\n\r\n; <<>> DiG 9.8.3-P1 <<>> euca-10-104-7-10.eucalyptus.euca-hasp.eucalyptus-systems.com @10.104.1.216 +recurse\r\n;; global options: +cmd\r\n;; Got answer:\r\n;; ->>HEADER<<- opcode: QUERY, status: NOERROR, id: 42118\r\n;; flags: qr aa rd ra; QUERY: 1, ANSWER: 1, AUTHORITY: 0, ADDITIONAL: 0\r\n\r\n;; QUESTION SECTION:\r\n;euca-10-104-7-10.eucalyptus.euca-hasp.eucalyptus-systems.com. IN A\r\n\r\n;; ANSWER SECTION:\r\neuca-10-104-7-10.eucalyptus.euca-hasp.eucalyptus-systems.com. 60 IN A 10.104.7.10\r\n\r\n;; Query time: 222 msec\r\n;; SERVER: 10.104.1.216#53(10.104.1.216)\r\n;; WHEN: Wed Oct 16 12:32:15 2013\r\n;; MSG SIZE  rcvd: 94\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n*Steps*\r\n\r\n* Set up a Eucalyptus 3.3.2 cloud\r\n* Enable Eucalyptus DNS\r\n* Make sure experimental.dns.recursive.enabled is set to true, and do the following:\r\n** Test recursive lookup from within instance\r\n** Test recursive lookup from client outside the cloud\r\n* Change experimental.dns.recursive.enabled to false, and do the following:\r\n** Test recursive lookup from within instance\r\n** Test recursive lookup from client outside the cloud\r\n\r\n*Pertinent Data*\r\n\r\nTo turn off recursive lookups from external clients is a best practice for security and performance reasons.  Refer to [RFC-5358|http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5358.txt]\r\n\r\n*Workaround*\r\n\r\nN/A","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=spark","name":"spark","key":"spark","accountId":"557058:2ed923b8-7172-41f0-a425-8796bd9a62f9","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fec440044f6e652174838d59d9233f29?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dspark%26avatarId%3D10900%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fec440044f6e652174838d59d9233f29?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dspark%26avatarId%3D10900%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fec440044f6e652174838d59d9233f29?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dspark%26avatarId%3D10900%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fec440044f6e652174838d59d9233f29?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dspark%26avatarId%3D10900%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Sang-Min Park","active":false,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":nu